<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-719-414  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 719 414.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDGE on andamp; about ATandamp;T  June 25, 1990 v5 n100 p1(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EDGE Publishing 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>FDDI: ATandamp;T Microelectronics testing new device for physical layerof FDDI networks. (ATandamp;T's T7351 integrated circuit) (illustration)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   AT and T Bell Laboratories Inc. (product development).andO;Product:   AT and T Microelectronics T7351 (Integrated circuit) (testing).andO;Topic:     Integrated CircuitsTestingFiber Distributed Data Interface StandardNetworksComplementary Metal Oxide Semiconductors.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>FDDI: ATandamp;T MICROELECTRONICS TESTING NEW DEVICE FOR PHYSICAL LAYER OF FDDINETWORKSandM;ATandamp;T Microelectronics is working with selected computer and communicationscompanies to test an efficient, low-power integrated circuit that is thefirst to combine all the functions that implement the physical layer of fiberdistributed data interface networks (FDDI).andM;EDGE Note: FDDI is a standard set by the American National StandardsInstitute (ANSI) for high-capacity (100 megabits-per-second) data transferthrough lightwave systems such as local area networks.andP;  There are fourelements in the standard:  the physical media-dependent (PMD), the physical(PHY), the media access control (MAC), and the station management (SMT)elements.andM;Designed by ATandamp;T Bell Laboratories in complementary metal-oxide semiconductor(CMOS) technology, the new device being tested is about half the size ofintegrated circuits available from other vendors.andP;  System designers can saveup to 60 percent of board space at the physical layer.andP;  ATandamp;T's device is thefirst single-chip solution to implement the FDDI standard at the physicallayer.andM;The device integrates functions such as clock recovery, data elasticity,line-state detection, link-error monitoring, and smoothing.andM;ATandamp;T's device--the T7351 integrated circuit -- also requires far fewersupport devices by integrating some of the station management (SMT) functionsinto the chip.andP;  Because it is implemented in 0.9 micron CMOS (complementarymetal oxide semiconductor) technology, the new device draws only 800milliwatts -- less than half the power of any competing device.andP;  Low powerconsumption lets a designer incorporate more ports per concentrator unit at alower cost.andM;Because it meets ANSI standards, ATandamp;T's T7351 device is compatible with manyother manufacturer's devices for FDDI applications.andP;  Depending on customers'requirements, ATandamp;T will enable customers to use ATandamp;T's evaluation board forthe new device.andP;  As a result, designers can simulate and test applicationsfor the T7351 in their existing systems.andM;&quot;Our goal is to make it as easy as possible for system designers to buildFDDI networks,&quot; said Dick Koeltl, head of ATandamp;T Microelectronics' metal oxidesemiconductor operations.andP;  &quot;FDDI will do for fiber optics what Ethernet didfor coaxial cable.andP;  The FDDI market is ready to explode, and ATandamp;TMicroelectronics is actively testing leading-edge solutions that will beavailable by the end of this year.&quot;andM;The new ATandamp;T T7351 device can be used in fiber-optic local area networks tolink mainframes to each other or to peripherals such as high speed printers,or in new generations of workstations such as high resolution graphicsterminals.andM;The market for FDDI LANs alone is expected to grow from about $20 milliontoday to over $300 million over the next three to five years.andP;  Compared withLANs that use coaxial cable and copper wiring, fiber optic LANs offerincreased speed, higher reliability, and higher data security.andP;  FDDI networkscan carry information at speeds of up to 200 Mb/s, compared with 10 Mb/s forEthernet LANs.andP;  In addition, fiber can also transmit information over severalkilometers without electromagnetic interference problems.andM;The T7351 is available now to a limited number of customers in an 84-pinplastic quad fine pitch (PQFP) package.andP;  Targeted pricing is less than $75for production quantities.andP;  Samples and production quantities will be offeredin the fourth quarter of 1990.andO;</TEXT></DOC>